SOMETIMES APPEND NOT WORKS TRY EXTEND

.append()
The .append() method adds its argument as a single element to the end of the list. If you pass a list to .append(), it adds the entire list as a nested object.

Python

list_a = [1, 2, 3]
list_a.append([4, 5])

print(list_a)
Result: [1, 2, 3, [4, 5]] (The length increased by 1)

.extend()
The .extend() method iterates over its argument and adds each item to the list individually. It essentially "unpacks" the collection you provide.

Python

list_b = [1, 2, 3]
list_b.extend([4, 5])
 
print(list_b)
Result: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] (The length increased by 2)

